What is MythBox?
================
MythBox is a MythTV frontend for XBMC. 

Features:
  - Watch recordings with commercial skipping
  - Watch Live TV
  - Create and update recording schedules
  - View upcoming recordings 
  - Enhanced program guide
  - TV show and movie fanart downloaded from tvdb, tmdb, imdb, and google image search
  - View MythTV stats (tuners, jobs, loadavg, etc)
  - Compatible with MythTV 0.21, 0.22, and 0.23
  - Add your own Twitter feeds

Requirements
================
  
  All Platforms
    - A working MythTV backend
    - MythTV recordings directory(s) and/or storage groups accessible via the local 
      filesystem (the machine running XBMC) pre-mounted using nfs, samba, afp, etc.   

  Linux
    - XBMC Camelot 9.11 running a recent 32-bit or 64-bit distro (Ubuntu, Debian, Fedora, Gentoo, Arch, OpenSuse, etc) 
    - ffmpeg installed as /usr/bin/ffmpeg (Ubuntu/Debian users: sudo apt-get install ffmpeg)

  Mac OSX
    - XBMC Camelot 9.11 running on Mac OSX 10.5 (Leopard) - Intel only 

  Windows
    - XBMC Camelot 9.11 running on Windows XP, Vista, or Windows 7 (32-bit or 64-bit)
  
  MythBox does *not* work on the XBox.
  
  
Installation
================
  
  1. Extract mythbox.tar.gz to the following directory:
     Linux   : ~/.xbmc/scripts 
     Mac     : ~/Library/Application Support/XBMC/scripts
     Windows : C:\Documents and Settings\[user]\Application Data\XBMC\scripts
     Vista   : C:\Users\[user]\AppData\Roaming\XBMC\scripts
           
  2. Launch XBMC
  
  3. From the main XBMC screen, select Scripts
  
  4. From the Scripts screen, select MythBox 
  
  5. You'll be sent straight to the Settings screen (with an error message). 
     Fill in all the settings and click on the 'Test Settings' button until 
     you get a 'Settings OK' message.
  
  6. Exit the Settings screen & enjoy!


Keybindings/Remote Control
============================================================================
Context         Keyboard       MCE Remote     Action
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Navigation      Esc            -              Go back to the previous screen
                Backspace      Back/Previous  Go back to the previous screen 
                M              Win Button     Go back to the main menu
                
----------------------------------------------------------------------------                   
Playing Video   X              Stop           Stop video
                Space          Pause          Pause video
                PrtScrn        Record         Take screenshot
                I              Info           Show program info                               
                O              Guide          Show audio/video/fps stats
                Z              OK             Toggle zoom modes
                Tab            N/A            Toggle video mode
                \              N/A            Toggle fullscreen  
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Home Window    Context Menu    TV Guide Btn   Activate popup menu to delete
Coverflow                                     or re-record the selected
                                              recording
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Recording      PgUp           Channel Up      Show previous recording
Details Window PgDown         Channel Dn      Show next recording
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
TV Guide       PgUp           Channel Up      Scroll TV guide up one page
               PgDown         Channel Dn      Scroll TV guide down one page
               R              FastRewind      Scroll TV guide left one page
               F              FastForward     Scroll TV guide right one page                                                    
               ?              End             Scroll TV guide forward 1 day
               ?              Begin           Scroll TV guide back 1 day  
----------------------------------------------------------------------------


